Continental Advisors’ Investment Principles
Continental Advisors has adopted the following principles under which it endeavors to operate its business and that serve as cultural guideposts for the firm:
 



It is the client’s money


Eat your own cooking


Be disciplined and humble


There are diseconomies of scale to active portfolio management


Nobody can predict where the stock market is going


Stocks represent an economic interest in the future cash flows of a business


Risk management is more important than total rate of return


Focus on investment strategies where you think you have a competitive advantage - skip everything else


Use all available investment instruments to optimize the risk and return profile of the portfolio


Leverage can be and has been deadly - use it with great care


People who sustain the worst losses are usually those who overreach


Worst reality is always worse than the worst case scenario - the real investment world does not behave according to historical standard deviations


 
 


























